  </sponsors>
  <source>The University of Hong Kong</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Globally, hepatitis B virus (HBV) infection is the most common form of chronic hepatitis.
      There are still a lot of uncertainties on how infants acquired HBV leading to the development
      of chronic HBV infection despite active and passive immunoprophylaxis. The investigators
      would like to carry out a prospective study to answer the following questions:

        1. the paternal, maternal and obstetric factors leading to immunoprophylaxis failure

        2. the prevalence of immunoprophylaxis failure in Hong Kong
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
